OL,3,CBritain is 'sick man of Europe' ` new
OL,4,Creport into health of the nation
OL,6,FThey examined absence trends pre-2020
OL,7,Fand compared them to the number off
OL,8,Fwork due to long-term sickness at the
OL,9,Fstart of 2024.
OL,11,FThey found that 900,000 more workers
OL,12,Fwere off work due to long-term
OL,13,Fsickness compared to what would have
OL,14,Fexpected to have occurred had pre-2020
OL,15,Ftrends continued.
OL,17,FAnd this figure may grow significantly
OL,18,Fhigher, they warned.
