OL,3,CBritain is 'sick man of Europe' ` new
OL,4,Creport into health of the nation
OL,6,F"We lag our peers on health outcomes,
OL,7,Fthe number of people with a long-term
OL,8,Fcondition is rising, and people are
OL,9,Fspending longer in poor health. And
OL,10,Fhealth is worsening throughout the
OL,11,Flife course ` bringing real challenges
OL,12,Ffor children, adolescents, working-age
OL,13,Fadults, and those who have retired.
OL,15,F"That is, the nation's health
OL,16,Fchallenges have reached historic
OL,17,Fproportions."
